@startuml failsafe_escalation_to_output_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title FailSafe Escalation To Output Signal Flow\n(CGW -> IVI / CLU)

participant "ADAS / body boundary\nwarning sources" as Sources #E8F7E8
participant "CGW\nfail-safe / gateway owner" as CGW #FFF4CC
participant "IVI\nwarning render owner" as IVI #E8F0FE
participant "CLU\ncluster warning owner" as CLU #E8F0FE

== Boundary / Gateway Intake ==

Sources -> CGW : decision seams + timeout / boundary inputs
activate CGW
CGW -> CGW : warningPathStatus / e2eHealthState / boundaryAlive
CGW -> CGW : failSafeMode = 0 / 1 / 2
CGW -> CGW : selectedAlertEffectiveLevel / Type
CGW -> CGW : selectedAlertGateReason = 1 / 2 / 3
note right of CGW
Representative escalation rules
- timeoutClear or dead boundary -> gate reason 1/2
- failSafeMode >= 1 -> effective level floor 4
- fallback alert type when decision type is 0
end note
CGW -> IVI : CoreState::selectedAlertEffectiveLevel
CGW -> IVI : CoreState::selectedAlertEffectiveType
CGW -> IVI : CoreState::selectedAlertGateReason
CGW -> IVI : Core::timeoutClear
CGW -> IVI : Core::failSafeMode
CGW -> CLU : same effective seams
CGW -> CGW : publishFailSafeState()
CGW -> CGW : publishGatewayState()
CGW -> CGW : publishObjectSafetyState()
deactivate CGW

== IVI Escalated Warning Render ==

activate IVI
CGW -> IVI : effective seams + timeoutClear
IVI -> IVI : deriveWarningTextCode()
IVI -> IVI : updateBackboneAlertState()
IVI -> IVI : UiRender::warningBeepState
IVI -> CLU : frmClusterWarningMsg
IVI -> CLU : frmClusterNotifMsg
note right of IVI
Representative outputs
- warning text code
- notif / popup state
- warning beep state
end note
deactivate IVI

== CLU Escalated Display ==

activate CLU
CGW -> CLU : effective seams
IVI -> CLU : frmClusterWarningMsg / frmClusterNotifMsg
CLU -> CLU : keep alert visible when\nselectedAlertGateReason > 0 or timeoutClear == 1
deactivate CLU

note over Sources, CLU
Representative runtime chain
1. Boundary or transport issue reaches CGW
2. CGW escalates effective alert and gate reason
3. IVI converts escalation into warning text / beep
4. CLU keeps the escalated warning visible to the driver
end note

@enduml
